onduct monthly feedback surveys to gauge resident wellbeing and future initiatives.\n\n\n**Outlining Core Functionality**\n\nI\'m now integrating detailed requirements based on the user\'s input, focusing on robust citizen authentication with role-based access. I\'m prioritizing the house number for sign-up and detailed issue tracking, including location, AI-powered categorization, image reporting, and severity levels. I\'m also planning the admin dashboard with trend monitoring and contractor performance visualization. I\'ll include performance tracking for elected officials and payment views.\n\n\n**Implementing Contractor Portal**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the contractor portal, allowing sign-ups and issue management, including bidding and payment requests. I\'m focusing on automated notifications for status updates and monthly resident wellbeing surveys for community feedback. Based on the user\'s feedback, the Firebase setup is confirmed, and I can now build a robust, full-stack application.\n\n\n**Verifying Firebase Setup**\n\nI\'m now verifying the Firebase setup based on the user\'s confirmation. I\'m checking if I need to call the `set_up_firebase` tool after the user accepted terms in the UI. I checked the skill and path, but it seems there is a path issue: the file `/skills/system_skills/firebase-skill/SKILL.md` is empty, or nonexistent, or not properly configured. I\'ll search for matching files in `/skills` to find the skill documentation.\n\n\n"
