    thinking: "**Refactoring AuthModal Styling**\n\nI\'m currently focused on refactoring the `AuthModal.tsx` component, aiming for a \"High Density\" aesthetic. Specifically, I\'m updating the core background and text colors to `bg-slate-50 text-slate-900` instead of the original `bg-slate-900 text-slate-100`. This is the immediate focus now.\n\n\n**Revising AuthModal Design**\n\nI\'m now revising the design for the `AuthModal` in `AuthModal.tsx`. I\'m going for a high-density, white-background card look, bordered by `border-slate-300`. Inputs will have white or light slate backgrounds with dark text and placeholders. Quick demo login buttons will appear as dense, bordered tables or tiles with dark labels and emerald accents. I\'m also planning to implement a tech-badge-style header with emerald accents and solid, dark-themed create/sign-in buttons. I am also planning on modifying the entire return block in `/src/components/AuthModal.tsx` from lines 79 to 316.\n\n\n"
