  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing Project Readiness**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the project\'s build and linting have both passed flawlessly. I\'m now cross-referencing `metadata.json` and `.env.example` to ensure no declarations are overlooked. Excellent news \342\200\223 I\'ve successfully implemented the requested PWA support with offline caching for view-only content, and the project is now ready.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully added full-stack Progressive Web App (PWA) support to the project with optimized offline caching for view-only mode.\n\n### \360\237\214\237 Implemented Features\n\n1. **Scalable PWA Icon (`/public/icon.svg`)**:\n   - Designed a crisp vector icon styled in **Slate-900** and **Emerald Green** with a central community star, matching the applet\'s styling. This SVG dynamically scales for all devices, satisfying standard launcher and maskable criteria.\n\n2. **Web App Manifest (`/public/manifest.json`)**:\n   - Defined essential manifest keys including `name`, `short_name`, `theme_color`, `background_color`, and adaptive icon configurations across standard dimensions (`72x72` to `512x512`) using the scalable SVG.\n\n3. **Advanced Service Worker (`/public/service-worker.js`)**:\n   - **Static Assets Cache**: Implemented a **Stale-While-Revalidate** strategy for standard files (HTML, JS, CSS, fonts) to make pages load fast and work reliably offline.\n   - **View-Only API Cache**: Intercepts `GET` requests to `/api/*` using a **Network-First** strategy. When online, it updates the cache dynamically; when offline, it falls back to the cached results, ensuring that issues, surveys, and notifications remain viewable.\n   - **Bypasses Writes**: Configured `POST`, `PUT`, and `DELETE` API requests to go straight to the network without caching, preventing accidental stale write states while offline.\n\n4. **SEO & iOS Integration (`/index.html`)**:\n   - Linked the manifest file, defined the slate `#0f172a` browser theme color, and configured Apple mobile-web-app capabilities with clean status bar stylings.\n\n5. **App Shell Registration (`/src/main.tsx`)**:\n   - Registered the Service Worker smoothly on page load, avoiding blocking the main thread during initial render.\n\n6. **Offline Banner Detector (`/src/App.tsx`)**:\n   - Integrated a native window online/offline event listener in a React hook.\n   - Designed an ambient, modern **amber warning banner** that slides in at the very top of the interface whenever the user goes offline, clearly notifying them: *\"You are currently offline. Viewing cached local reports and surveys (read-only mode).\"*\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 995652210
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
